text.tspan: Most Yallourn and Loy Yang units operating with little
to no headroom, but some response is visible. It is
possible sampling error (as per Stanwell units)
might be obscuring withdrawn PFR in Loy Yang
and Yallourn units (uptick in power output). Following
dip in power output could be result of control
settings to return units to scheduled output
Frequency in VIC returns to NOFB soon after disturbance, so it is difficult to determine
if load controllers have withdrawn unit's PFR because of or regardless of system frequency
